{
  "texts": [
    "Although the theory has been proposed, little if any evidence supports it.",
    "Encouraging people, and especially children, to berate or socially mistreat AI on the theory that it will help them become kinder toward people seems ill-advised to us.",
    "In contrast, the existing evidence suggests that human treatment of AI can sometimes result in a practice effect, which carries over to how people treat each other.",
    "Those practice effects could either result in social harm, if antisocial behavior is practiced, or social benefit, if pro-social behavior is practiced.",
    "The moral issue of perceiving consciousness in AI and suggested regulations As stated at the beginning of this article, we do not take sides here on the question of whether AI is conscious."
  ]
}